{{Infobox animal | name = Claude | image = Albino Alligator 2008.jpg | caption = Claude in his swamp at the [[California Academy of Sciences]] | species = ''[[Alligator mississippiensis]]'' | gender = Male | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|9|15|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Florida]] | occupation = Exhibit | known = | owner = [[California Academy of Sciences]] | weight = {{convert|222|lb|kg}} }}
'''Claude''' is an [[Albinism in biology|albino]] alligator (''[[American alligator|Alligator mississippiensis]]'') at the [[California Academy of Sciences]]. Claude lacks the pigment [[melanin]], which results in his skin color. He also has poor eye-sight due to his albinism.<ref name="SFGate" />
==Background== Claude was born on 15 September 1995 in Florida weighing {{convert|2|oz|g}}.<ref name="SFGate">{{cite web | url=http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/Albino-alligator-Claude-to-mark-15th-birthday-3253032.php | title=Albino alligator Claude to mark 15th birthday | publisher=SFGate | date=14 September 2010 | accessdate=8 August 2015 | author=Guthrie, Julian}}</ref> He weighs {{convert|222|lb|kg}} and is {{convert|9|ft|5|in|m}} long.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://abc7news.com/archive/9134317/ | title=Famous gator gets a check-up | date=10 June 2013 | accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref> He has 76 teeth.<ref name="SFGate" />
He was in danger in the wilderness owing to albinism which did not allow him to camouflage into his surroundings like other alligators. There are only a couple of dozen known albino alligators in the world, all in captivity.<ref>{{cite web|title=Albino alligator Claude to mark 15th birthday|url=http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/Albino-alligator-Claude-to-mark-15th-birthday-3253032.php#photo-2401962|website=SF gate|accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref> Claude was taken to the [[California Academy of Sciences]] in 2008.<ref name="SFGate" /> Claude's toe was amputated after developing an infection from being bitten by another alligator.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sfchronicle.com/bayarea/article/Tough-times-for-koi-continue-as-S-F-aquarium-6071694.php | title=Tough times for koi continue as S.F. aquarium looks to sever ties | publisher=San Francisco Chronicle | date=9 February 2015 | accessdate=8 August 2015 | author=Rubenstein, Steve}}</ref>
Claude appears completely white because he lacks the pigment melanin. This is due to destruction of pigment-forming cells known as melanocytes.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Swamp|url=http://www.calacademy.org/exhibits/the-swamp|website=California Academy of Sciences|accessdate=7 August 2015}}</ref>
