<ref>James Coates, [http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1997-07-25/business/9707250166_1_jango-netbot-software-from-microsoft-corp "Shopping Net Cast On The Web: Software Searches Sites For Products On Consumers' Lists"], ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'', July 25, 1997.</ref>  In addition, the company operated  [[MetaCrawler]], a [[metasearch engine]], before licensing it to Go2Net. In October 1997, Netbot was acquired by the [[Excite]] portal for $35M.<ref>
