'''Theodorus Martinus''' "'''Ted'''" '''de Boer''' (born 11 May 1943, [[Uithoorn]])<ref name=uva>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.uva.nl/en/about-the-uva/organisation/staff-members/content/b/o/t.m.deboer/t.m.deboer.html |title=prof. dr. T.M. (Ted) de Boer |publisher=University of Amsterdam |date= |accessdate=14 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=album>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.albumacademicum.uva.nl/cgi/b/bib/bib-idx?type=simple;lang=nl;c=ap;rgn1=entirerecord;q1=Boer;x=0;y=0;cc=ap;view=reslist;sort=achternaam;fmt=long;page=reslist;size=1;start=19 |title=Prof. mr. dr. T.M. de Boer, 1943 - |language=Dutch |publisher=Album Academicum University of Amsterdam |date= |accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> is an emeritus professor of [[Conflict of laws|private international law]] and [[comparative law]] at the [[University of Amsterdam]].
==Biography== De Boer studied law at [[Utrecht University]] and obtained a [[Master of Laws]] degree there in 1969. Two years later he earned a further Master of Laws degree at [[New York University]]. De Boer obtained his [[Doctor of Juridical Science]] at the University of Amsterdam in 1987.<ref name=uva/> He started as professor in 1987 and he retired in October 2003. He then continued as unpaid professor until 2010.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.peacepalacelibrary.nl/plinklet/index.php?ppn=30663841X |title=Voor Ted de Boer bij zijn afscheid als hoogleraar aan de Universiteit van Amsterdam per 1 oktober 2003 |publisher=Peace Palace Library |date= |accessdate=14 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=album/>
De Boer was elected a member of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/3902 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814152518/https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/3902 |title=Ted de Boer |publisher=Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences |date= |archive-date=14 August 2016}}</ref>
